  "prompt": "How do I change One Plus 3 ringtone?",
  "response": "Here's how to change the ringtone on your OnePlus 3:\n\n**Method 1: Through Settings**\n\n1.  **Open Settings:** Find the Settings app icon on your home screen or app drawer and tap it.\n2.  **Go to Sound (or Sound & Vibration):** Scroll down in the Settings menu and look for an option labeled either \"Sound\" or \"Sound & Vibration\". Tap on it.\n3.  **Find Phone ringtone (or Ringtone):** Within the Sound settings, you'll usually see options related to volume, vibrations, and ringtones. Look for an option labeled \"Phone ringtone\", \"Ringtone\", or similar. Tap on it. (If you have dual SIMs, you may see options like \"SIM 1 ringtone\" and \"SIM 2 ringtone\". Choose the one you want to change.)\n4.  **Choose a Ringtone:** A list of pre-installed ringtones will appear. Tap on a ringtone to preview it.\n5.  **Select Your Ringtone:** Once you've found the one you like, simply tap on it to select it.  The phone will usually automatically save your selection.  In some cases, you might have a button like \"OK\" or \"Apply\" to confirm your choice.\n6.  **Exit Settings:** You can now exit the Settings app.\n\n**Method 2:  Using File Manager (for Custom Ringtones)**\n\nIf you want to use a custom ringtone (a song or sound file you downloaded), follow these steps:\n\n1.  **Locate Your Audio File:** Make sure the audio file (usually in .mp3 format) is on your phone's internal storage or SD card.  Use your file manager app (like \"Files\" or \"File Manager\") to find it.\n2.  **Copy or Move to the Ringtones Folder (Recommended):**\n    *   For the ringtone to appear in the system's ringtone list, it's best to place it in the designated \"Ringtones\" folder.\n    *   Use your file manager to copy or move the audio file to the \"Ringtones\" folder. This folder is usually located in the internal storage directory (you might have to create it if it doesn't exist).  The path would be something like `Internal Storage/Ringtones`.\n3.  **Follow Steps in Method 1:** Now, go back to the Settings app and follow the steps in Method 1 (Settings > Sound > Ringtone). The custom ringtone you added to the \"Ringtones\" folder should now appear in the list of available ringtones. Select it.\n4.  **Alternative (If the above doesn't work):**\n     *   If, after moving/copying the file to the ringtones folder, the custom ringtone still doesn't show in the settings, try the following when you are in ringtone selection:\n          *  Look for a \"+\" or \"Add Ringtone\" option somewhere in the ringtone selection screen. This often lets you browse your phone's storage to select an audio file directly.\n5.  **Select your ringtone:** Choose the new ringtone.\n\n**Troubleshooting Tips:**\n\n*   **Check Volume:** Make sure your phone's volume isn't muted or set too low.\n*   **File Format:** Ensure your custom ringtone file is in a compatible format like .mp3.\n*   **Permissions:** Make sure the Settings app has permission to access storage, if needed.  You can check this in Settings > Apps > Settings > Permissions.\n*   **Restart Your Phone:** Sometimes, a simple restart can resolve minor software glitches that might prevent the ringtone from being set correctly.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to easily change the ringtone on your OnePlus 3 to your desired sound. Good luck!\n",
